    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-08-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-08-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="579" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d579">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">Julian
                                    Pauncefote</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Newport</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-08-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 18,
                                1893</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to my telegram of to day
                            and to your note of the 9th instant, I have the honor to inform you that
                            I have received a telegram from my Government in which it is stated that
                            the German Government is ready to take charge of Mataafa and eleven
                            other chiefs and keep them in the Marshall Islands. They propose at the
                            same time that the three powers divide the cost of their keep. Her
                            Majesty’s Government hope that the United States Government will approve
                            of this proposal in which they concur.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Julian
                            Pauncefote.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
